                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>On some fols. the word qum or qwǝm ("stop", "stand") is written in red by a secondary hand (?) in the intercolumn or in the upper margin. In addition a red curved line with one or two circle at each end is drawn occasionally between two words of the main text (e.g., <locus target="16r">16r</locus>, 17r, 94r, 101rb, 111ra). This term may indicate a particular passage of the text or a certain section or may serve as a reminder for the reader to command that the congregation "stands up" (cp. UhlPal 91).</note>
                  </msItem>
